        "content": "**Gap:** one source raising must not abort the whole run (`except Exception` swallow-and-log). Also untested: `concurrency` semaphore actually bounds parallelism, and unknown `ats` value raises `ValueError` from `fetch_source`.\n\n```python\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_all_isolates_source_failures(monkeypatch):\n    async def boom(client, source): raise RuntimeError(\"network down\")\n    async def ok(client, source): return [Job(source=\"x\", company=\"y\",\n                                              external_id=\"1\", title=\"t\", url=\"u\")]\n    monkeypatch.setitem(FETCHERS, \"broken\", boom)\n    monkeypatch.setitem(FETCHERS, \"fine\", ok)\n    jobs = await fetch_all([{\"ats\": \"broken\"}, {\"ats\": \"fine\", \"company\": \"y\"}])\n    assert len(jobs) == 1\n\ndef test_fetch_source_unknown_ats_raises():\n    with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"unknown ATS\"):\n        asyncio.run(fetch_source(None, {\"ats\": \"nope\"}))\n```\n\n---\n\n",
