        "title": "4. `store.py` — SQLite dedup logic, zero tests, high risk",
        "content": "\n**Untested:** `Store.__init__`/`_migrate`, `diff` (new/changed/unchanged paths), `_insert`, `_update`, `get_meta`/`set_meta` (including the `ON CONFLICT` upsert), `added_since` (string-comparison ordering claim), `count`, context-manager protocol.\n\n**Gaps:**\n- `diff` returns correct `(new, changed)` split and leaves untouched rows alone (`last_seen` bumps but not `content_hash`)\n- Same job key seen twice in one `diff()` call (in-batch dedup — is it even handled? Looks like it isn't — second occurrence would try `INSERT` after the row already exists from step 1 in-memory query — actually since it queries DB per-job and inserts immediately, a duplicate within the same batch will correctly hit the \"already exists\" branch on its second occurrence. Worth locking in.)\n- `_migrate` adds `salary_range` column to a legacy DB missing it\n- `set_meta` upsert (insert then update same key)\n- `added_since` ordering and strict `>` boundary (not `>=`)\n\n```python\n",
        "level": 2
      },
      {
        "title": "tests/test_store.py",
        "content": "import pytest\nfrom models import Job\nfrom store import Store\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef store(tmp_path):\n    with Store(tmp_path / \"test.db\") as s:\n        yield s\n\ndef _job(ext_id=\"1\", title=\"SWE\"):\n    return Job(source=\"greenhouse\", company=\"acme\", external_id=ext_id,\n               title=title, url=\"u\", location=\"NYC\")\n\ndef test_diff_new_job_is_inserted_and_reported_new(store):\n    new, changed = store.diff([_job()])\n    assert len(new) == 1 and changed == []\n    assert store.count() == 1\n\ndef test_diff_unchanged_job_reports_neither(store):\n    store.diff([_job()])\n    new, changed = store.diff([_job()])\n    assert new == [] and changed == []\n\ndef test_diff_changed_content_reports_changed(store):\n    store.diff([_job(title=\"SWE\")])\n    new, changed = store.diff([_job(title=\"Senior SWE\")])\n    assert new == [] and len(changed) == 1\n\ndef test_diff_duplicate_key_within_same_batch(store):\n    j = _job()\n    new, changed = store.diff([j, j])\n    assert store.count() == 1  # second occurrence treated as unchanged, not a crash\n\ndef test_meta_roundtrip_and_upsert(store):\n    assert store.get_meta(\"k\") is None\n    store.set_meta(\"k\", \"v1\")\n    store.set_meta(\"k\", \"v2\")\n    assert store.get_meta(\"k\") == \"v2\"\n\ndef test_added_since_strict_boundary_excludes_equal_timestamp(store):\n    store.diff([_job()])\n    ts = store.conn.execute(\"SELECT first_seen FROM jobs\").fetchone()[0]\n    assert store.added_since(ts) == []  # strictly-after, not >=\n\ndef test_added_since_orders_oldest_first(store):\n    store.diff([_job(\"1\", \"A\")])\n    store.diff([_job(\"2\", \"B\")])\n    rows = store.added_since(\"1970-01-01T00:00:00+00:00\")\n    assert [r[\"external_id\"] for r in rows] == [\"1\", \"2\"]\n\ndef test_migrate_adds_salary_range_to_legacy_schema(tmp_path):\n    import sqlite3\n    path = tmp_path / \"legacy.db\"\n    conn = sqlite3.connect(str(path))\n    conn.execute(\"\"\"CREATE TABLE jobs (key TEXT PRIMARY KEY, source TEXT, company TEXT,\n        external_id TEXT, title TEXT, url TEXT, location TEXT, department TEXT,\n        employment_type TEXT, posted_at TEXT, content_hash TEXT,\n        first_seen TEXT, last_seen TEXT)\"\"\")\n    conn.commit(); conn.close()\n    with Store(path) as s:\n        cols = {r[\"name\"] for r in s.conn.execute(\"PRAGMA table_info(jobs)\")}\n        assert \"salary_range\" in cols\n```\n\n---\n\n",
