        "content": "\n**Untested (and testable without touching Claude/network):** `cmd_db_new` (watermark truncation-at-group-boundary logic), `cmd_db_mark` (ISO validation, `--now`, neither-arg error), `_normalize_ats` (ATS character rules, must skip `<style>`/`<script>` blocks and tag attributes), `_chrome_bin` discovery order, argv parsing in `main()` (mode-word vs flag split).\n\n**Gaps — the trickiest one nobody has verified:**\n- `cmd_db_new`'s truncation logic: \"truncate only at `first_seen` group boundaries\" — this is exactly the kind of off-by-one that needs a test with >`limit` rows spanning 3 timestamp groups.\n- `_normalize_ats` must NOT rewrite characters inside `<style>`/`<script>` or inside tag attributes, only body text.\n- `cmd_db_mark` rejects a non-ISO watermark with exit code `2` and doesn't write to the store.\n- `main()`'s flag/mode-word split (`words[:i]` vs `words[i:]` at first `-`-prefixed token).\n\n```python\n",
